        overview_fact_kicker: "Officially verified today",
        overview_fact_title: "Today's updates",
        overview_fact_date_prefix: "Updated on",
        overview_fact_1_title: "Model recommendations aligned to surfaces",
        overview_fact_1_desc: "Re-checking `codex/models` confirms the recommended family is now GPT-5.6: Sol for complex/high-value work, Terra for everyday work, and Luna for fast repeatable work. GPT-5.5 remains available as the previous-generation frontier model, `gpt-5.3-codex-spark` remains a Pro research preview, and `gpt-5.2`/`gpt-5.3-codex` remain deprecated for ChatGPT-authenticated Codex.",
        overview_fact_2_title: "GPT-5.6 model family structure",
        overview_fact_2_desc: "Current Codex, What's new, and API latest-model docs all point to GPT-5.6. In Codex, choose Sol/Terra/Luna by task shape, use Max for the hardest single-task reasoning, and use Ultra when the work divides cleanly across subagents. In the API, `gpt-5.6` routes to `gpt-5.6-sol`. Programmatic Tool Calling, Multi-agent beta, explicit prompt caching, persisted reasoning, max reasoning effort, Pro mode, and original/auto image detail preservation belong to the Platform/API lane, not general Codex setup.",
        overview_fact_3_title: "Plans and team pricing clarified",
        overview_fact_3_desc: "Quickstart still says every ChatGPT plan includes Codex and keeps App, IDE extension, CLI, and Cloud as official choices. OpenAI's July 9 ChatGPT Work announcement says the updated Mac/Windows desktop app is globally available with Chat, Work, and Codex on every plan, including Free. Pricing now lists GPT-5.6 Sol/Terra/Luna in the Plus, Pro, Business, and API Key usage tables, while Pro still includes `gpt-5.3-codex-spark` as a research-preview benefit. Fast mode remains documented for GPT-5.5/GPT-5.4 only, so usage limits, speed mode, and direct API pricing should be checked separately.",
        overview_fact_4_title: "IDE and Windows paths clarified",
        overview_fact_4_desc: "The IDE docs cover VS Code-style editors, Xcode, and JetBrains across macOS, Windows, and Linux. The Windows app docs split the flow clearly: install the ChatGPT desktop app from the official download or Microsoft Store, optionally use `winget install Codex -s msstore`, run the native agent in PowerShell, select `Ask for approval` beneath the composer for sandbox protection, restart after switching the agent to WSL2, and choose the integrated terminal separately.",
        overview_fact_5_title: "App workflows reflected",
        overview_fact_5_desc: "Cross-checking `Introducing the Codex app`, the April 16 `Codex for (almost) everything` post, and the current `app/features` / `app/automations` / `app/settings` docs helped move worktrees, built-in Git, the integrated terminal, skills, automations, thread automations, chats, the in-app browser, artifact preview, image generation, background computer use, memories, context-aware suggestions, broader plugins, role-specific plugins, broader annotations, multiple terminal tabs, SSH devboxes, and the summary pane earlier in the guide. Sites is now documented as a Business/Enterprise preview for saving and deploying OpenAI-hosted production URLs, with Enterprise RBAC/admin enablement, save-version versus deploy-version review, access modes, and runtime-secret management in the Sites panel called out. The June 1 OpenAI/AWS announcement and Codex Amazon Bedrock docs are reflected as an enterprise/provider deployment path with AWS-managed authentication, account controls, and billing, not as a ChatGPT plan-limit change.",
        overview_fact_6_title: "Config/API/plugin flow refreshed",
        overview_fact_6_desc: "The guide keeps current config, permissions, plugin, and cloud/runtime notes aligned, while moving Platform/API guidance to GPT-5.6. API users should treat `gpt-5.6` as an alias for `gpt-5.6-sol`, evaluate reasoning effort including `max`, and separate API-only features such as Programmatic Tool Calling, Multi-agent beta, explicit prompt caching, persisted reasoning, Pro mode, and original/auto image detail from Codex product setup.",
