        s3_rec_note: "💡 The latest `codex/models` guidance says to start with the GPT-5.6 family. Default Power uses `gpt-5.6-sol` with medium reasoning; choose Sol for difficult or high-value work, Terra for everyday work, and Luna for fast, repeatable, high-volume tasks. Max gives a single task more reasoning time, while Ultra coordinates subagents for large tasks that divide cleanly. If Ultra is missing from the desktop app slider, enable Ultra in model picker slider under Settings > Configuration. Pricing now lists GPT-5.6 Sol/Terra/Luna in Plus, Pro, Business, and API Key usage tables. Fast mode is still documented for GPT-5.5/GPT-5.4 only, so keep model choice and speed mode as separate decisions. `gpt-5.5` remains available as the previous-generation frontier model, `gpt-5.3-codex-spark` remains a Pro research preview, and `gpt-5.2`/`gpt-5.3-codex` remain deprecated for ChatGPT-authenticated Codex.",
